				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(3.5) Ability to Solo
<br />

<br />
(1) Ability to make pp with innate skills
<br />

<br />
(3) Ability to make pp through farming
<br />

<br />
*Note: WTF does this do for a class balance score?*
<br />

<br />
(4) Group contribution
<br />

<br />
(3) Raid contribution
<br />

<br />
(5) Self Sufficiency
<br />

<br />
(4) Desirability in groups
<br />

<br />
(3) Perception by other classes
<br />

<br />
(2) Equipment availability
<br />

<br />
(3) Useful upgrades
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
(4) Overall balance IMO
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Added notes:
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I personally do not think that ability to make cash matters to a class balance score. Anyone and Everyone can make money in all sorts of ways. Even without special solo ability. If you are determined enough, everyone can make a ton of plat. It's not hard if you learn certain tricks or get lucky on randoms or spend time developing tradeskills...
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I also do not see what a Shadowknight's personal knowledge about what a Beastlord can do as anything to do with balance. All we need to do is tell them, and boom, solved. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

