			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings;
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
(3) Ability to solo effectively.
<br />

<br />
(1) Ability to make money with innate abilities.  What does this have to do with balance.  Seems more like a question a druid would ask.
<br />

<br />
(3) Ability to make money through farming.  What does this have to do with balance.  Seems more like a question a druid would ask.
<br />

<br />
(3) Group contribution.   In the questionaire, you say skills, however, I took this to mean skills and abilities.  If it is simply skills, then this number drops to 1.
<br />

<br />
(3) Raid contribution.  Unfortunately, this one varies drastically based on level and type of raid.  For example, level 51 offers nothing but DPS to the raid, but at 60+, our utility lends a great deal to certain types of raids.
<br />

<br />
(4) Self-Sufficiency.
<br />

<br />
(4) Desirability in Groups.   This one is a bit too tricky.  The class is still new enough that many people still don't understand the full capabilities of a Beastlord.  When they do understand, we are very much wanted, but the members of the group may not know enough about the class yet.
<br />

<br />
(3) Perception of Class.  See desirability above.
<br />

<br />
(2) Equipment.  There is very little gear currently available that is Beastlord only.  Further, there are no Beastlord specific effects/functions to the gear that is out there.
<br />

<br />
(3) Expansions and Upgrades.   This one really should be N/A, however, VI/SoE has done a lot of work trying to get us balanced, outside the actual balance cycles.   I can only imagine what we will be when VI/SoE gets around to the hybrid balance cycle.
<br />

<br />
(4) Overall.   We are not quite balanced yet, but overall I am very satisfied with the Beastlord as it currently stands. Investigator Aaeorn, Fiftieth Circle Redeemed Thief Catcher of Xev.
<br />
Baron Kaatt, Fifty-Four Year Old Khati Sha Primalist of Xev.
<br />
Aaeorm, Enchantement Technician of the Twenty-Ninth Tier of Xev.
<br />
Proud member of Dissonance
<br />

<br />

<br />

